codex-storage-perf.task:
Fix 3 performance issues in src/notes/storage.rs:

1. FTS TRIGGER FIX (critical): In init_notes_db(), the notes_au trigger fires on every UPDATE that mentions title/content columns, even when values don't change. Replace the trigger with one that uses a WHEN guard to only fire when values actually differ:
   DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS notes_au;
   CREATE TRIGGER notes_au AFTER UPDATE ON notes
   WHEN OLD.title <> NEW.title OR OLD.content <> NEW.content
   BEGIN
     INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, content) VALUES('delete', OLD.rowid, OLD.title, OLD.content);
     INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, content) VALUES (NEW.rowid, NEW.title, NEW.content);
   END;

2. SEARCH LIMIT (major): In search_notes(), add LIMIT 200 to the FTS query to prevent unbounded result sets from blowing up memory. Add it after the ORDER BY bm25(notes_fts) clause.

3. BATCH TRASH DELETE (major): Add a new pub fn delete_all_deleted_notes() -> Result<()> that deletes all soft-deleted notes in one SQL statement: DELETE FROM notes WHERE deleted_at IS NOT NULL (inside a transaction). This replaces the per-note loop.

